summary: This is a notification from the chambers of Judge Alison J. Nathan regarding the case US v. Maxwell (20cr330). It informs counsel that Judge Nathan has granted additional time for two sets of supplemental briefing and references an attached order to be docketed the following morning.

persons.name: Alison J. Nathan
persons.context: Presiding judge in the case US v. Maxwell who has granted additional time for supplemental briefing.

events.title: Order Granting Extension for Supplemental Briefing
events.description: Judge Alison J. Nathan grants the parties additional time to file two sets of supplemental briefing in the case US v. Maxwell.

keyFacts: Judge Alison J. Nathan is presiding over the criminal case US v. Maxwell (docket number 20cr330).
The judge granted an extension for the parties to file two sets of supplemental briefing.
The notification was sent on November 11, 2021, regarding an order dated November 10, 2021.
